    "updated_at": "2019-11-27T20:50:02Z",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "The general problem is that different parts of the truffle system use different mechanisms for acquiring and normalizing paths.  This leads to differences in casing and separator (`/` vs `\\`).  Since the path is used as a key in a map, this means you end up with two keys for a particular thing in the map, one of which gets populated and the other doesn't, which then leads to invalid artifacts.",
